<H3> <TI>   CDR Members Take Hostages at Foreign Minstry </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2102215094 Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la 
Republique Rwandaise in French 1800 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2102215094 </F>
<F P=104>  Kigali Radiodiffusion Nationale de la 
Republique Rwandaise </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A demonstration by the Coalition for the Defense of 
the Republic [CDR] is being held in Kigali. At 1600, members of 
the Coalition for the Defense of the Republic sealed off the 
roundabout outside the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and hoisted 
their party's flag in front of the ministry. The CDR party 
wants to claim the seat reserved for it in the future National 
Assembly, as stipulated in the Arusha Peace Accord. As I speak 
to you, the demonstration is continuing and the personnel from 
the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Cooperation, men and women, 
are being held hostage by the demonstrators. 

