<F P=101> Eritrea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leaves for Jordan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA1902214094 Asmara Voice of the Broad Masses of Eritrea in 
Tigrigna 1600 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA1902214094 </F>
<F P=104>  Asmara Voice of the Broad Masses of Eritrea </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tigrigna </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yemeni President General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and 
his delegation were seen off today from Asmara International 
Airport by President Isayas Afewerki; Foreign Minister Muhammad 
Ahmad Sharifo; Ali Sayyid Abdallah, the minister of internal 
affairs; (Yesuf Yeshaq), head of the Middle East desk at the 
foreign office; and Mahmmud Jabra, the Eritrean ambassador to 
Yemen. 
  President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih told journalists before 
leaving that he was pleased with his visit in Eritrea and his 
meetings with President Isayas and other Eritrean Government 
officials. 
  He also said his visit would have a positive effect on the 
efforts being made to maintain Yemeni's unity and the relations 
between the two countries. He added that he was now leaving for 
Amman, Jordan, to sign an agreement with the various Yemeni 
political parties. He expressed the hope that the agreement 
would solve Yemen's problems. He urged the three main political 
parties working to create a coalition to implement the agreement 
seriously. 
  Noting Eritrea's role in solving Yemen's problems, President 
'Ali 'Abdallah Salih said Eritrea's efforts had been very 
successful. He said Eritrea's role in bringing the various 
political parties together had been very significant. 

</TEXT>

