<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Council To Invite Alliance for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2102143594 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1400 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2102143594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The negotiating council has decided to send a 
written invitation to the Freedom Alliance inviting them to join 
the council. Negotiating council Chairman Pravin Gordhan said 
he had received feedback that members of the alliance would 
appreciate an invitation requesting some kind of a response to 
the constitutional proposals. Mr. Gordhan said the council 
expected the alliance to respond to the invitation by early 
evening. The council is processing a package of constitutional 
concessions and amendments to secure the Freedom Alliance's 
participation in the election. 
  The government and the ANC [African National Congress] 
earlier submitted their proposals to the negotiating council at 
Kempton Park. The Freedom Alliance did not attend the meeting 
at the World Trade Center. 

</TEXT>

