<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Alliance Meets in Pretoria, Affirms Nonparticipation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2102164294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2102164294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Freedom Alliance has indicated that the proposed 
amendments to the interim constitution are inadequate and the 
alliance will not participate in the election. Alliance 
Chairman Rowan Cronje said in Pretoria, after a meeting of the 
executive of the alliance, that the concession on the double 
ballot was welcome. However, there was still no autonomy for 
regions to impose taxes, and no guarantee of a volkstaat 
[homeland]. Concessions on the entrenchment of provincial 
powers were also insufficient. 

</TEXT>

