<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Meyer: Sovereign Zulu State `Impossible' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2002173094 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2002173094 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The minister of constitutional affairs, Mr. Roelf 
Meyer, says it will be impossible for [Zulu] King Zwelithini to 
have a sovereign state. Speaking at Noordgezicht near 
Johannesburg, Mr. Meyer said, however, that there was nothing 
against the king having control over his subjects. He said he 
saw the best solution as writing the king's sovereignty into a 
provincial constitution. 

</TEXT>

