<H3> <TI>   Clashes Between UNITA, Government Forces Continues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Heavy Fighting Reported in Huila </H4>
<F P=102> MB2102130194 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 
1100 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2102130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Observers in Angola say heavy fighting between UNITA 
[National Union for the Total Independence of Angola] and 
government forces is continuing in the southern Huila Province. 
They say many government tanks and armored vehicles with heavy 
artillery are moving towards UNITA positions in the province. 
Air support is being provided to the tanks and armored vehicles 
by fighter aircraft and bombers from the Angolan Air Force. The 
latest fighting is centered in an area between the towns of 
Cacula and (Negola). 

</TEXT>

