increased FALA activity virtually throughout Lunda Sul Province 
[words indistinct] the UNITA forces attacked five defensive FAA 
positions in Mona Quimbundo, (Caiaze), (?Dembos) [words 
indistinct] FAA's response resulted in four FALA soldiers killed 
and another three captured. The FAA forces also captured 
assorted weapons and ammunition. 
  That note also said that the FAA forces released 270 men, 
women, and children from UNITA captivity in the area of 
(?Dembos) [words indistinct] meanwhile, three other civilians 
turned themselves over to the authorities. 
  Despite the (?attacks), the situation is under the full 
control of the government forces. 

