<H3> <TI>   Clashes Between UNITA, Government Forces Continues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Twelve FAPLA Soldiers Killed </H4>
<F P=102> MB2202093394 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 0600 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2202093394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The war situation prevails in Lunda Sul Province, 
with government troops on the offensive. This was revealed 
yesterday by the Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola 
[FALA] North West Command. The source said that over the 
weekend the Popular Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor 
Party [MPLA-PT] troops attacked the National Union for the Total 
Independence of Angola [UNITA] in Caiaza area, on Saurimo-Ndala 
and Lucapa-Saurimo roads. There were also clashes in the Mona 
Quimbundo area, where the People's Armed Forces for the 
Liberation of Angola [FAPLA] abducted some peasants in the 
villages. The North West command has described these operations 
as coward provocations to which FALA responded promptly, killing 
12 FAPLA soldiers. 

