<H3> <TI>   Unomoz Updates Troop Confinement Figures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2102194894 Maputo Radio Mozambique Network in Portuguese 
1705 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2102194894 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Mozambique Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Mozambican Government has sent more than 2,500 
soldiers to the assembly areas over the last six days; 43 
percent of its soldiers have now been confined. 
  Meanwhile, 540 Mozambique National Resistance [Renamo] 
soldiers turned up at their assembly areas over the same period; 
55 percent of Renamo's soldiers have now arrived in the assembly 
areas. 
  According to the UN Operations in Mozambique, Renamo has 
sent 
its first 71 men to [name indistinct], in Maputo Province. 
Those men came from Salamanga. 

