<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Eritrea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yemen's Salih Meets Afewerki, Comments on Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN1802175794 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1700 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1802175794 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Yemeni Presidential Council, arrived in Asmara 
at noon today on a visit to the State of Eritrea. During his 
visit he will hold talks on bilateral relations and ways of 
bolstering them, in addition to developments in the Horn of 
Africa. 
  He was received at Asmara Airport by Isayas Afewerki, 
president of the State of Eritrea. [passage omitted] 
  Immediately after his arrival, the Presidential Council 
chairman held talks with President Afewerki on issues of mutual 
interest and means of bolstering bilateral cooperation. 
  Developments in the Horn of Africa and international issues 
of mutual concern were also discussed. Discussions also tackled 
developments in our country in light of the document of accord 
concluded by the Political Forces Dialogue Committee, which is 
due to be signed by the concerned parties in the Jordanian 
capital, Amman, next Sunday. 
  The brother Presidential Council chairman expressed his 
appreciation for the good offices extended by Eritrea so that 
our country can overcome the difficult challenges it faces as a 
result of the political crisis. He said the accord document 
will be signed in the Jordanian capital, Amman, on Sunday. He 
expressed hope that, after the signing of the accord, all will 
move to the stage of practical implementation in a manner that 
will bolster Yemen's unity march, our democratic policies, and 
stability in our country. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-25529 </DOCNO>
