<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Negotiating Council Presents New Constitution Package </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2102120894 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1100 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2102120894 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The new package of constitutional amendments have 
been presented to the multiparty negotiating council in Kempton 
Park by the government and the ANC [African National Congress], 
who said the amendments were aimed at addressing the concerns of 
the Freedom Alliance and enhancing the legitimacy of the interim 
constitution. The tabled amendments confirm earlier versions of 
the constitutional concessions announced last week. The 
proposals include concessions on self-determination to address 
right-wing demands for a volkstaat [homeland]. These are 
supplemented by a proposal that a volkstaat council be 
established by members of Parliament to pursue the concept of a 
volkstaat after the election. No members of the Freedom 
Alliance attended this morning's meeting of the negotiating 
council. The concessions will also allow provinces to write 
their own constitutions and to create their own legislative and 
executive structures. A two-ballot system is also proposed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-25530 </DOCNO>
