<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sources Say Transitional Institutions Postponed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2202143194 Paris AFP in French 1327 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2202143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kigali, 22 Feb (AFP) -- The installation of the 
transitional Parliament and broad-based government, scheduled 
for this afternoon, has been postponed indefinitely following 
last night's assassination of the public works minister, it was 
learned from many sources here. A spokesman of the UN 
Assistance Mission in Rwanda had indicated late this morning 
that the installation of the transitional institutions was still 
scheduled despite the assassination of Mr. Gatabazi, who was 
shot dead close to his house. The installation of these 
institutions should have taken place in early January, under the 
terms of the peace accord signed last August after three years 
of civil war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

