<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Rwanda </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hutu Political Leader Assassinated by Demonstrators </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2202155194 Paris AFP in French 1526 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AB2202155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kigali, 22 Feb (AFP) -- Martin Bucyana, chairman of 
the Coalition for the Defense of the Republic, which seeks to 
defend the interest of Hutus, was killed today by an angry crowd 
following the assassination yesterday of Felicien Gatabazi, 
Rwandan minister of public works and energy, Rwandan radio 
announced. 
  Bucyana was attacked by demonstrators of Gatabazi's party, 
the opposition Social Democratic Party, at Butare in the south 
of the country. He died after being admitted to hospital, the 
radio explained. 

</TEXT>

