Angola. 
  Asked to comment whether those developments posed a threat 
to 
the region's stability, a source with the General Staff of the 
Armed Forces for the Liberation of Angola said: We will 
continue to follow a policy of good neighborliness. We will not 
interfere in the domestic affairs of sovereign governments, 
though provocations will never be tolerated. The source urged 
the Namibian people not to allow circles in the Government of 
Namibia to plunge their country into a senseless war. 

