<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Congo </F>
<H3> <TI>   Buffer Force Deployed in Southern Brazzaville </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2002131694 Paris Radio France International in French 0630 
GMT 20 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2002131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris Radio France International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] A buffer force is today being deployed in the 
southern suburbs of Brazzaville in Congo, which have been the 
scene of bloody ethnic clashes in recent months. All sides 
agreed to the deployment of the force after the cease-fire 
agreement signed on 30 January by deputies from the four regions 
of the south of the country. The force is being sent to keep 
the belligerents apart and to contain the various militias in 
their zones. This force of 400 men is due to be deployed today. 
It already began to take up its positions on the night of 
Friday to Saturday [18-19 February]. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

