<F P=100> CENTRAL AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Gabon </F>
<H3> <TI>   PDG Member Killed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2302100094 Libreville RTG Chaine Nationale Radio Network 
in French 0800 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2302100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Libreville RTG Chaine Nationale Radio Network 
in French 0800 GMT 23 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Political violence broke out in Libreville 
yesterday. Radio-Tele Liberte was destroyed early yesterday 
morning by the Armed Forces, which stormed the radio station 
located at Terre-Nouvelle. After Radio-Tele Liberte was 
destroyed, opposition supporters retaliated by killing (Jean 
Kamougue-Komo), a member of the Gabonese Democratic Party [PDG]. 
  The government daily L'UNION has reported the death of an 
unidentified person at Yayi crossroads, who was killed as the 
security forces were destroying a barricade. Tension has been 
high in Libreville since 21 February when the Federation of Free 
Trade Unions called for an indefinite general strike. 

</TEXT>

