<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Italian Troops Come Under Attack in Mogadishu </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2302125294 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1212 GMT 
23 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2302125294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The former site of the Italian Embassy in Mogadishu, 
which is currently the headquarters of an Italian contingent in 
the country, has come under Somali fire. Guards returned fire, 
but it seems that none of the attackers were injured. 
  Meanwhile, in Nairobi, General Aidid declared that he was 
not 
opposed to UN peacekeeping troops protecting aid conveys in 
Somalia. 

</TEXT>

