<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   No Plans To Send Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2402155394 Johannesburg Afrikaans Stereo Radio Network in 
Afrikaans 1400 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2402155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Afrikaans Stereo Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Afrikaans </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Organization of African Unity [OAU] will not 
send troops to monitor the situation in South Africa. This was 
said by the secretary general of the OAU, Dr. Salim Ahmed Salim, 
after a meeting with Foreign Affairs Minister Pik Botha in 
Pretoria. Mr. Salim said that peace could be brought about only 
by South Africans. He said that South Africa was part of the 
African family of nations, and that it would be welcomed as a 
member of the OAU. 

</TEXT>

