<H3> <TI>   Government Troops Sink Nigerian Boats in Clashes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB2702091094 London BBC World Service in English 0600 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB2702091094 </F>
<F P=104>  London BBC World Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "African News" program] </F>
  [Text] State radio in Cameroon has given an account of 
fighting which took place early this month in the Bakassi 
Peninsula area which is disputed with Nigeria. It quoted a 
Cameroonian military official as saying 10 Nigerian boats, each 
carrying about 10 soldiers, had attacked a Cameroonian position. 
The radio said two of the boats were sunk and one Cameroonian 
soldier was killed and one wounded in the exchange nine days 
ago. A delegation from Cameroon has since held talks in Nigeria 
aimed at reducing tension. 

</TEXT>

