<F P=100> EAST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Eritrea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Somalia's Aidid Meets With Afewerki in Asmara </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2502205594 Asmara Voice of the Broad Masses of Eritrea in 
Tigrinya 1600 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2502205594 </F>
<F P=104>  Asmara Voice of the Broad Masses of Eritrea </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Tigrinya </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] General Muhammad Farah Aidid, the leader of a 
Somalian opposition group, met President Isayas Afewerki after 
arriving in Asmara today. The main objective of his visit to 
Eritrea is to discuss issues affecting Somalia and the Horn of 
Africa. He was met on arrival at Asmara International Airport 
by Foreign Minister Muhammad Sharifo and Mr. Girma Asmerom, the 
head of the Africa desk at the Foreign Ministry. 
  General Farah Aidid extensively discussed with President 
Isayas Afewerki issues affecting Somalia and the Horn of Africa, 
noting that the security situation in Somalia was improving and 
stabilizing, and that the various political organizations were 
reconciling and engaging in dialogue. Having stated that the 
Somali people could solve their own problems without the 
intervention of foreign (?forces), he noted that the efforts of 
President Meles and other East African leaders to solve 
Somalia's problem were the best and most appropriate. The 
efforts of President Isayas and the state of Eritrea to solve 
Somalia's problem were highly appreciated by the Somali people. 
  For his part, President Isayas noted that the Eritrean 
Government believed that Somalia's problem could only be solved 
by the Somalis themselves, and that it opposed foreign 
intervention. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

