<F P=101> Somalia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aidid Official Condemns Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  EA2602191694 (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People in Somali 1700 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2602191694 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Radio Mogadishu Voice of the 
Great Somali People </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Somali </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Dr. 'Abd al-Aziz Shaykh Yusuf, the deputy chairman 
of the Somali National Alliance, SNA, who is also the chairman 
of the Southern Somali National Movement [SSNM], spoke on behalf 
of the SNA chairman, the SNA deputy chairman, SNA supporters, 
and on his own behalf today. He stated that the Somali people 
had been greatly shocked by monstrous massacre of Muslims 
praying at the holy Hebron Mosque in occupied Palestine. Dr. 
'Abd al-Aziz said the callous act had generated shock throughout 
the world, particularly the Islamic world. He prayed to god to 
grant the souls of the departed eternal peace and to provide 
solace to the bereaved families, the Palestinian people and the 
Muslims of the world. The SNA deputy chairman appealed to the 
Somali people to pray for the departed Muslims. 

</TEXT>

