<H3> <TI>   UNITA Radio Reports Rabat Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2602131694 Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro in 
Portuguese 1200 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2602131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jamba Voz da Resistencia do Galo Negro </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Eduardo dos Santos, president of the Popular 
Movement for the Liberation of Angola-Labor Party, MPLA-LP, left 
the French capital this morning for Morocco, where he is 
scheduled to meet King Hassan II in Rabat. They will discuss 
King Hassan II's peace proposal for Angola. 
  Meanwhile, diplomatic sources have said that Jose Eduardo 
dos 
Santos is disappointed with Angolan Ambassador to France 
Boaventura Cardoso's work. Ambassador Cardoso had prepared the 
Futungo de Belas Palace chieftain's visit to France. The 
MPLA-PT leader is also unhappy about a less than truthful report 
produced by Foreign Affairs Minister Venancio de Moura 
suggesting improved bilateral relations. The general opinion is 
that MPLA-PT leader's three-day visit to France was a thorough 
fiasco. 
  French President Francois Mitterrand took a firm position 
and 
made it clear that his country did not wish to compromise the 
Lusaka peace talks in any way. The government led by Prime 
Minister Edouard Balladur supported President Francois 
Mitterrand's positions. [passage omitted] 
  Using his constitutional powers, French President Mitterrand 
yesterday warned Acting President Eduardo dos Santos that France 
only supports a negotiated settlement to the Angolan crisis. 
The upshot is that Engineer Eduardo dos Santos will be 
returning home quite disappointed. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

