<F P=100> SOUTHERN AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Namibia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Legal Cooperation Agreement Signed With South Africa </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2602155594 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 
1100 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2602155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] South Africa and Namibia have signed an agreement to 
facilitate the easier administration of justice between the two 
countries and have expressed hopes for increasing regional legal 
cooperation. Signed in Walvis Bay by the South African justice 
minister, Mr. Kobie Coetsee, and his Namibian counterpart, Mr. 
Ngarikutuke Tjiriange, the agreement was the first of its kind 
between South Africa and a neighboring state. It creates the 
legal scope for enforcement of maintenance orders, civil 
judgments, and cross border subpoenas, and criminal court 
orders. The two governments also agreed to investigate 
reciprocal legislation to better facilitate searches and seizure 
of illegal goods. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

