94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2702050794 </F>
<F P=104>  Maputo Radio Maputo </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mozambican Foreign Minister Dr. Pascoal Mocumbi has 
warned that his government is considering using force to remove 
members of the Malawian paramilitary body, the Young Pioneers, 
who have crossed illegally into Mozambique last December. Dr. 
Mocumbi said his government will ask the Supervisory and Control 
Commission, the body in charge of implementing the peace 
agreement between the Mozambican Government and Renamo 
[Mozambique National Resistance], to become involved. This is 
because the government would need to use troops to bring the 
Young Pioneers under control, but under the terms of the peace 
agreement with Renamo, any such troop movements must be approved 
by the commission. 

