<H3> <TI>   Minister Regrets U.S. Group's Funding of Opposition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2702163694 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in 
English 1600 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2702163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zimbabwe's foreign affairs minister says plans by a 
United States organization to help fund the political opposition 
in Zimbabwe amounts to subversive interference in the country's 
internal affairs. In an interview published in Harare, Dr. 
Nathan Shamuyarira said the International Republican Institute 
was funded by security agents of big powers. The Zimbabwean 
Government strongly regretted the plan to help the opposition. 
He said it was tantamount to interference in the internal 
affairs of Zimbabwe. Dr. Shamuyarira said there was a danger 
that the American funding could lead to subversion. Zimbabwean 
opposition parties should fund themselves locally. He said the 
money they received from the international organizations was 
dirty money. 

