<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   AVF, ANC Leaders Meet To Discuss Standerton Issues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2802071594 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0623 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2802071594 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Johannesburg Feb 28 SAPA -- Afrikaner Volksfront 
[AVF, Afrikaner National Front] leaders Tienie Groenewald and 
Constand Viljoen would meet an African National Congress [ANC] 
delegation in Standerton on Monday [28 February] (this) morning 
to discuss a variety of issues affecting the Eastern Transvaal 
town, the ANC said. ANC spokesman Ronnie Mamoepa confirmed an 
ANC delegation led by Mathew Phosa would meet the two Boer 
leaders in Standerton to discuss: 

  -  the declaration of Standerton as part of a "volkstaat" 
[homeland]; 
  -  a planned ANC march through the town on Wednesday (March 2) 
after a previous march in the town ended in confrontation 
between ANC supporters, rightists and the police; 
  -  the consumer boycott affecting the area and other issues. 

    Mr Mamoepa said the meeting was due to get underway at 9am 
at 
the Standerton town council offices and could last "some time". 

</TEXT>

