<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Supporters Urged To `Sharpen Weapons' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2702103394 Johannesburg SUNDAY NATION in English 27 Feb 94 
p 3 </F>

<F P=103> MB2702103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SUNDAY NATION </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Pan Africanist Congress [PAC] supporters should 
"sharpen their weapons" because there are bad times ahead, 
Azanian People's Liberation Army (Apla) political commissar 
Romero Daniels said yesterday. Speaking before a crowd of 
10,000 which filled Umtata's Independence Stadium for the 
funeral of Apla commander Sabelo Phama, Daniels said attempts to 
establish a volkstaat [Afrikaner homeland] amounted to 
provocation. Daniels said the "absurd boerestaat" [Boere state] 
advocated by General Constand Viljoen could be regarded as 
"provocation for the continuation of the war." 
  "The moratorium on armed struggle declared by the PAC -- and 
fully endorsed by Apla -- was not a defeat of the freedom 
fighters. We are political fighters giving the masses of Azania 
the chance to decide their own form of government. So to Apla 
fighters, we say: be ready, be on the alert, sharpen your 
weapons for any eventuality by the enemy, be combat-ready. We 
are heading for bitter times." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

