<F P=102>  MB2402132294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1223 GMT 24 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2402132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Durban Feb 23 SAPA -- The Democratic Party [DP] in 
Natal announced its election candidates for the provincial 
legislature and National Assembly this week, many of them 
leading community members and administrators. Heading the 
40-member provincial list for the National Assembly are MPs Mike 
Ellis, Mahmoud Rajab, and Carol Charlewood. 
  Other candidates include leading Malcolm Wallis, SC [Senior 
Counsel], farmer and MP Wessel Nel, and environmental campaigner 
and attorney Oliff d'Oliviera. 
  Leading the 80-member list for the provincial legislature is 
recently-elected Natal DP Chairman Roger Burrows. Others are 
Phoenix businessman Omie Singh, Queensburgh Mayor Dave Upfold 
and retired police station Commander Mike Reddy. 
  A number of the candidates hold positions on both lists. 

