<H3> <TI>   Bombs Discovered at IFP Durban Headquarters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2802105494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1024 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> MB2802105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg SAPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Durban Feb 28 SAPA -- Police detonated an explosive 
device at the Inkatha Freedom Party's [IFP] headquarters in 
Durban on Monday morning, IFP spokesman Ed Tillet said. Police 
spokesman Maj Bala Naidoo was not immediately available to 
comment, but police had cordoned off the area around the IFP 
office in Albany Grove and were apparently attending to another 
"bomb" in a nearby parking lot, said Mr Tillet. 
  "The first bomb was in the building," said Mr Tillet."The 
other was outside in the garage where transport for our national 
headquarters is kept." 

</TEXT>

