<F P=100> REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Norway Lifts Remaining Economic Sanctions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  MB2602155394 Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio in English 
1100 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> MB2602155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Johannesburg Channel Africa Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Norway has lifted its last economic sanctions 
against South Africa. It repealed a 1986 ban on oil exports and 
oil shipments and other economic sanctions imposed in 1987 to 
help remove apartheid. Norway said developments in South Africa 
and plans for elections in April this year had made sanctions 
obsolete. Another contributing factor was the United Nations 
General Assembly resolution last October in which member nations 
were urged to follow African national Congress leader Nelson 
Mandela's request to end sanctions. Norway was one of the first 
countries to impose sanctions against South Africa and to give 
aid to the African National Congress. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

