<H3> <TI>   Taipei Official Departs for Jakarta for APEC Meeting </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2801084194 Taipei CNA in English 0720 GMT 28 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2801084194 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Debbie Kuo] </F>
  [Text] Taipei, Jan. 28 (CNA) -- Huang Yen-Chao, 
director-general of the Board of Foreign Trade [BOFT], left 
Friday [28 January] for Jakarta to attend a senior officials 
meeting of the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation [APEC] forum. 
The meeting begins Monday and ends Friday. 
  BOFT Deputy Director-General Lin Yi-fu is accompanying 
Huang. 
  The meeting is the first ever of APEC senior officials, and 
is also the first in a series of APEC meeting to be hosted by 
Indonesia this year, Huang said at the airport. The other 
meetings will be held in May, September and November. The 
November meeting will probably be a ministerial or even 
presidential meeting, Huang said. 
  Among the discussion topics at next week's meeting will be a 
joint proposal by Taiwan and the United States that APEC develop 
guidelines on small- and medium-business development 
cooperation, Huang said. 
  The APEC Investment and Trade Committee, established at the 
November APEC meeting in Seattle, will also convene for the 
first time in Jakarta, he added. 

</TEXT>

